news.title: Kerala: Karuvannur Service Cooperative Bank casts shadow on property mortgage rules
news.para: As per cooperation department sources, many cooperative banks and institutions are resorting to the practice of extending multiple loans on the security of the same property by citing government rules in this regard.

news.title: Sohna: Built without nod, Nature Valley colony razed by DTCP
news.para: The builder, who was developing the colony under the project name ‘Nature Valley’ in Kiranki and Bhogpur villages of Sohna, had already constructed boundary walls, guard rooms, road network, light poles and other amenities and was planning to sell the farmhouses built on one-acre land .

news.title: Maharashtra: 30,000 co-operative housing societies await elections to plan redevelopment
news.para: Maharashtra Housing Federation vice-chairman Suhas Patwardhan on Wednesday said those societies had been waiting for long to conduct the elections that could not be held because of the pandemic. Of these 30,000 housing societies, 4,000-5,000 are from Pune.

news.title: High realty circle rates flummox flat buyers in Kolkata
news.para: The circle rate of a complex being developed in Tollygunge has been increased from Rs 4,180 per sq ft to Rs 9,900 per sq ft in August, nearly a month after the budget proposed a 10% reduction in circle rate along with a 2% cut in stamp duty till October 30.

news.title: AP Asia Opportunistic Holdings gets CCI approval for stake-buy in JSW Cement
news.para: "Commission receives notice under Green Channel filed by AP Asia Opportunistic Holdings for acquisition of approx. 12.55% equity share capital of JSW Cement and is deemed approved," the regulator said in a tweet.

news.title: Housing sales may rise 30% in 2021; to remain below pre-covid levels: Report
news.para: According to Anarock research, housing sales are expected to increase 30 per cent year-on-year (y-o-y) to 1,79,527 units across seven cities in 2021 from 1,38,344 units last year.

news.title: Maharashtra: Housing e-registration pilot project likely next month
news.para: The registration department is getting ready by ensuring that maximum developers are enrolled under the process and they have reached out to the builders’ association ahead of commencement of the pilot project.

news.title: MGF files FIR against Emaar officials over 'fraudulent transfer' of land
news.para: MGF Developments Ltd, with its subsidiary companies, have complained in the FIR that Emaar officials, fraudulently and unauthorisedly, forged Board Resolutions of MGF subsidiary companies and executed general power of attorney (GPA) in favour of Emaar in respect of land owned by the subsidiaries of MGF.

news.title: Builders only understand colour of money or jail term: SC
news.para: ​The top court directed that Rs 15 lakh be deposited by real estate firm Ireo Grace Realtech Pvt Ltd to National Legal Service Authority and Rs two lakh to the home buyers towards the cost of litigation, whose refund was not paid as directed by the top court.

news.title: NHB disburses over Rs 30,000 crore in interest subsidy under PMAY
news.para: The PMAY offers up to 3 percentage points in interest subsidy on low-cost housing loans (at 6.5 per cent) but caps the one-time subsidy at Rs 2.35 lakh per eligible borrower.

news.title: US: Housing construction slumps 7% in July to 1.53 million units
news.para: The July decline put home construction at a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 1.53 million units, the Commerce Department reported Wednesday. It was the slowest pace since April but was 2.5% higher than a year ago.

news.title: Chandigarh administration okays draft construction & demolition waste policy
news.para: UT adviser Dharam Pal said his aim is to recycle 100% C&D waste. The UT will give different options to residents to bring C&D waste to its plant at Industrial Area.

news.title: Delhi-based realtors sent to judicial custody in multi-crore fraud case
news.para: Sushant Mutreja and Nishant Mutreja were arrested on August 16 following which the court sent them to the custody of the Serious Fraud Investigation Office (SFIO) for two days where they were questioned on the alleged fraudulent transactions.

news.title: Jamshedpur: JREDA to light up Golmuri with 1,650 solar LEDs
news.para: JREDA will bear the subsidy part while the remaining cost of the installation scheme will be incurred by the MLA, under Local Area Development (LAD) scheme, as per the agreement reached between the two parties.

news.title: Bengaluru: Realtor lands in soup for building site in 'green zone'
news.para: Pashupathi Prasad, revenue inspector, Bidarahalli hobli, said: “A complaint has been lodged against Gowda of ABD Legacy project and 11 others for building a plot on agricultural land that falls in the ambit of so-called green zones. They have not availed the permission from the competent authorities.’’
